00:17:40.690 --> 00:17:43.690
Today it is known as Potswali.

00:17:43.690 --> 00:17:49.690
In about 59 C.E., the Apostle Paul arrived here by boat as a prisoner.

00:17:49.690 --> 00:17:57.690
From here, Paul will now begin the long journey to Rome, where he would eventually stand before Caesar himself.

00:17:57.690 --> 00:18:02.690
One of the most famous Roman highways is called the Appian Way.

00:18:02.690 --> 00:18:07.690
It averages 6 meters or 20 feet in width.

00:18:07.690 --> 00:18:10.690
And was paved with large lava blocks.

00:18:10.690 --> 00:18:16.690
It was on this very road that pulled travel to the city of Rome.

00:18:16.690 --> 00:18:23.690
Along the way, Paul eventually came to a busy 3D center known as the Marketplace of Apius.

00:18:23.690 --> 00:18:30.690
And a leader for the north was a rest area, like an inn, known as the Three Taverns.

00:18:30.690 --> 00:18:38.690
Having heard about Paul coming, Christians from Rome organized a group of brothers to meet the Apostle aboard of these stops.

00:18:38.690 --> 00:18:46.690
Acts 28-15 tells us that, upon seeing them, Paul thanked God and took courage.

00:18:46.690 --> 00:18:50.690
Next, we come to the impressive ruins of Boston, Tika.

00:18:50.690 --> 00:18:58.690
